Account fields and dimensions
Availability by ad type
Report types
The Amazon Ads API supports a number of report types based on campaign entity structure. Depending on the ad type, campaign performance can be broken down by various dimensions including campaign, ad group, ad, keyword, target, and ASIN.

Account fields and dimensions
When working with reporting API v3, you'll encounter several account-related fields that ensure consistency between account management and reporting operations:

advertiserAccount.id: The primary account identifier used in report dimensions. This corresponds to the adsAccountId from the Accounts API and matches the value used in the Amazon-Ads-AccountId header.
Amazon-Ads-AccountId header: Use this header to specify which advertising account's data you want to retrieve. The value should match the advertiserAccount.id in your report results.
accessRequested accounts: When making requests that span multiple accounts, use this field to specify which accounts you want to include in your report.
The relationship between these fields ensures consistency between account management and reporting operations across all ad products.

Availability by ad type
 Note
Sponsored Brands reports are currently available in preview. During the preview period, data related to Sponsored Brands campaigns with flag isMultiAdGroupsEnabled=False won’t be available. Once version 3 reporting supports all Sponsored Brands campaigns, we will announce general availability in the release notes.
Each type of sponsored ad supports different report types and has a separate path defined.

