Amazon DSP
Daily benchmarks report for Amazon DSP advertiser
Weekly benchmarks report for Amazon DSP advertiser
Monthly benchmarks report for Amazon DSP advertiser
Benchmarks reports
Benchmark reporting provides standardized performance comparisons against category peer brands, allowing advertisers to contextualize performance, evaluate optimization opportunities, and confidently invest with Amazon Ads. It displays your brand’s category performance against benchmarks broken out by Amazon ad product, ad format, and campaign goal type.

Additional benefits of using Benchmarks:

Self-service access to standardized category benchmarks for planning and campaign optimization.
Report is provided at the brand level and is available for Amazon DSP and Sponsored Ads accounts.
Transparency attributes provide insight on peer set size.
Benchmarks are available starting from October 1, 2025 and update every 48 hours with the last campaign data.
 Note
You must be a brand owner or representative on Amazon Stores to be eligible for benchmarks reporting.
Benchmarks reporting is currently only available in the US.
Configurations
Configuration	Amazon DSP	Sponsored Ads
reportTypeId	dspBenchmarks	crossProgramBenchmarks
Maximum date range x time unit	395 days (monthly, weekly); 90 days (daily)	395 days (monthly, weekly); 90 days (daily)
Data retention	395 days	395 days
timeUnit	DAILY, WEEKLY, MONTHLY	DAILY, WEEKLY, MONTHLY
groupBy	brandCategoryBenchmarks	brandCategoryBenchmarks
format	CSV or GZIP_JSON	CSV or GZIP_JSON
All ad products
Base metrics
Sponsored Ads
campaignCountry, brand, browseCategory, adProduct, adFormat, campaignGoal, peerSetSize, date, startDate, endDate

Amazon DSP
advertiserId, advertiserName, campaignCountry, brand, browseCategory, adProduct, adFormat, campaignGoal, peerSetSize, date, startDate, endDate

Group by brandCategoryBenchmarks
Additional metrics: percentOfPurchasesNewToBrand, percentOfPurchasesNewToBrandP25, percentOfPurchasesNewToBrandP50, percentOfPurchasesNewToBrandP75, newToBrandPurchaseRate, newToBrandPurchaseRateP25, newToBrandPurchaseRateP50, newToBrandPurchaseRateP75, costPerNewToBrandPurchase, costPerNewToBrandPurchaseP25, costPerNewToBrandPurchaseP50, costPerNewToBrandPurchaseP75, ctr, ctrP25, ctrP50, ctrP75, cpc, cpcP25, cpcP50, cpcP75, cpm, cpmP25, cpmP50, cpmP75, completionRateVideoAd, completionRateVideoAdP25, completionRateVideoAdP50, completionRateVideoAdP75, costPerCompletedViewVideoAd, costPerCompletedViewVideoAdP25, costPerCompletedViewVideoAdP50, costPerCompletedViewVideoAdP75

Filters:

Amazon DSP

advertiserId
Sample calls
Sponsored Ads
Daily benchmarks report for Sponsored Ads advertiser
curl --location 'https://advertising-api.amazon.com/reporting/reports' \
--header 'Content-Type: application/vnd.createasyncreportrequest.v3+json' \
--header 'Amazon-Advertising-API-ClientId: amzn1.application-oa2-client.xxxxxxx' \
--header 'Amazon-Advertising-API-Scope: xxxxxxxxx' \
--header 'Authorization: Bearer Atza|xxxxxxxxxx' \
--data '{
    "name": "Sponsored Ads Benchmarks Report",
    "startDate": "2025-11-01",
    "endDate": "2025-11-07",
    "configuration": {
        "adProduct": "ALL",
        "groupBy": ["brandCategoryBenchmarks"],
        "columns": [
            "date",
            "campaignCountry",
            "brand",
            "browseCategory",
            "adProduct",
            "adFormat",
            "campaignGoal",
            "peerSetSize",
            "percentOfPurchasesNewToBrand",
            "percentOfPurchasesNewToBrandP25",
            "percentOfPurchasesNewToBrandP50",
            "percentOfPurchasesNewToBrandP75",
            "newToBrandPurchaseRate",
            "newToBrandPurchaseRateP25",
            "newToBrandPurchaseRateP50",
            "newToBrandPurchaseRateP75",
            "costPerNewToBrandPurchase",
            "costPerNewToBrandPurchaseP25",
            "costPerNewToBrandPurchaseP50",
            "costPerNewToBrandPurchaseP75",
            "ctr",
            "ctrP25",
            "ctrP50",
            "ctrP75",
            "cpc",
            "cpcP25",
            "cpcP50",
            "cpcP75",
            "cpm",
            "cpmP25",
            "cpmP50",
            "cpmP75",
            "completionRateVideoAd",
            "completionRateVideoAdP25",
            "completionRateVideoAdP50",
            "completionRateVideoAdP75",
            "costPerCompletedViewVideoAd",
            "costPerCompletedViewVideoAdP25",
            "costPerCompletedViewVideoAdP50",
            "costPerCompletedViewVideoAdP75"
        ],
        "reportTypeId": "crossProgramBenchmarks",
        "timeUnit": "DAILY",
        "format": "GZIP_JSON"
    }
}'
