Calling the MMM API
This tutorial outlines how to request and download reports for Marketing Mix Model (MMM).

Because MMM APIs are asynchronous, there are multiple steps to using the APIs:

Get brand groups
Review ASINs
Review campaigns
Request a report
Wait for the report to generate
Download the report
Before you begin
Complete required steps to get started with the MMM API.
Learn more about the inputs and outputs of the MMM data feed.
Ensure you're using the North America (NA) API endpoint (https://advertising-api.amazon.com).
Headers
In addition to the individual API parameters, the following header parameters are required for most of your calls.

Header	Description
Amazon-Advertising-API-ClientId	The client ID related to a Login with Amazon application.
Amazon-Advertising-API-Manager-Account	The ID of the manager account you registered with MMM.
Authorization	Login with Amazon token in the form of Bearer token.
Content-type	application/json
Listing brand groups
The first step is to get the brand group you would like to request data for. You will need to call the POST /mmm/v1/brandGroups/list endpoint.

Sample request
This sample shows a request for your approved brand groups.

curl --location 'https://advertising-api.amazon.com/mmm/v1/brandGroups/list' \
-H 'Amazon-Advertising-API-ClientId: amzn1.application-oa2-client.xxxxxxxxxx' \
-H 'Amazon-Advertising-API-Manager-Account: amzn1.ads1.ma1.xxxxxxxxxx' \
-H 'Authorization: Bearer Atza|xxxxxxxxxx' \
-H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
-d '{
  "countryCodeFilter": {
    "include": ["US"]
  }
}'
Sample response
A successful request results in a 200 response that includes an array of brand groups. Please note down a brandGroupId and we will use this in the next steps.

{
  "nextToken": null,
  "brandGroups": [
    {
      "brandGroupId": "68d71a07-a3ea-47f2-9051-df7fd08a64da",
      "brandGroupName": "Continuous Protection Sunscreen Lotion for Kids",
      "advertiserName": "Jack & Jill",
      "countryCode": "US"
    },
    {
      "brandGroupId": "d0145381-b4a9-41a0-83de-e56c8f07d712",
      "brandGroupName": "Running Shoes",
      "advertiserName": "Accent Athletics",
      "countryCode": "US"
    },
    {
      "brandGroupId": "23d7c364-0124-410b-b899-8475eddbafef",
      "brandGroupName": "Apparel",
      "advertiserName": "Accent Athletics",
      "countryCode": "US"
    }
  ]
}
Reviewing ASINs
You can review the ASINs in a brand group before running a report to verify that all expected products are present.

Use the brandGroupId returned in the previous step to call the GET products endpoint: GET /mmm/v1/brandGroups/{brandGroupId}/products.

Sample request
curl --location 'https://advertising-api.amazon.com/mmm/v1/brandGroups/xxxxx-xxxxx-xxxxx/products' \
-H 'Amazon-Advertising-API-ClientId: amzn1.application-oa2-client.xxxxxxxxxx' \
-H 'Amazon-Advertising-API-Manager-Account: amzn1.ads1.ma1.xxxxxxxxxx' \
-H 'Authorization: Bearer Atza|xxxxxxxxxx' \
-H 'Content-Type: application/json'
Sample response
A successful response contains the products sold within the last 3 years for the brand group.

If nextToken is not null, call the endpoint again with nextToken as a query parameter to get the next page of results.

A report will include the subset of these products with orders inside the report date range.

Review each product’s title and categories to confirm that it belongs in the brand group.

If you need to add or remove products from the brand group, you can create overrides for those ASINs.

{
  "nextToken": null,
  "products": [
    {
      "asin": "B0018OFKJS",
      "title": "Men's Stretch Performance Tank Top",
      "productGroup": "Apparel",
      "productCategory": "Men's Athletic",
      "productSubcategory": "Tops/Tees",
      "firstOrderDate": "2022-02-14",
      "lastOrderDate": "2024-06-13"
    }
  ]
}
Reviewing campaigns
You can also review the campaigns associated with the products in the brand group.

Use the same brandGroupId to call the GET campaigns endpoint: GET /mmm/v1/brandGroups/{brandGroupId}/campaigns.

Sample request
curl --location 'https://advertising-api.amazon.com/mmm/v1/brandGroups/xxxxx-xxxxx-xxxxx/campaigns' \
-H 'Amazon-Advertising-API-ClientId: amzn1.application-oa2-client.xxxxxxxxxx' \
-H 'Amazon-Advertising-API-Manager-Account: amzn1.ads1.ma1.xxxxxxxxxx' \
-H 'Authorization: Bearer Atza|xxxxxxxxxx' \
-H 'Content-Type: application/json'
Sample response
A successful response contains the Sponsored Ads and Amazon DSP campaigns run in the last 3 years that are associated with at least one ASIN in the brand group (i.e. the ASIN is featured or tracked in the campaign settings).

If nextToken is not null, call the endpoint again with nextToken as a query parameter to get the next page of results.

A report will contain the subset of these campaigns whose dates overlap the report date range.

You can create overrides to adjust the campaigns in the brand group.

{
  "nextToken": null,
  "campaigns": [
    {
      "campaignId": "7286325070001",
      "name": "FY24 Accent Athletics In-Market Campaign - Shirts",
      "startDate": "2024-01-01",
      "endDate": "2024-12-31",
      "adProduct": "SPONSORED_PRODUCTS"
    }
  ]
}
Creating overrides
Brand group overrides can be used to modify the products and campaigns in a brand group before running a report.

If your products and campaigns already look correct, you can skip ahead to request a report.

To add a product to a brand group, create an ASIN override with type INCLUDE. This will also add any campaigns associated with that ASIN to the brand group. To remove a product from a brand group, create an ASIN override with type EXCLUDE. Campaigns that are not associated with any other ASINs in the brand group will also be removed.

You can similarly include or exclude specific campaigns by their ID values.

The best practice is to create ASIN overrides first to see how that impacts the campaigns in the brand group. Then you can create campaign ID overrides as needed. To add an ASIN or campaign ID to a brand group, your manager account must have permission to access that data. You will receive a 403 error code for requests that are not permitted. Contact mmm-support@amazon.com if you are seeing unexpected permissions issues when creating overrides. Once overrides are created, you should review ASINs and review campaigns again to verify that everything looks correct before requesting a report.

Sample request
Up to 100 overrides can be created in each request.

See the API reference for all available parameters.

curl --location 'https://advertising-api.amazon.com/mmm/v1/brandGroupOverrides' \
-H 'Amazon-Advertising-API-ClientId: amzn1.application-oa2-client.xxxxxxxxxx' \
-H 'Amazon-Advertising-API-Manager-Account: amzn1.ads1.ma1.xxxxxxxxxx' \
-H 'Authorization: Bearer Atza|xxxxxxxxxx' \
-H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
-d '{
  "overrides": [
    {
      "brandGroupId": "23d7c364-0124-410b-b899-8475eddbafef",
      "overrideType": "INCLUDE",
      "identifierType": "ASIN",
      "identifierValue": "B0018OFKJS"
    },
    {
      "brandGroupId": "23d7c364-0124-410b-b899-8475eddbafef",
      "overrideType": "INCLUDE",
      "identifierType": "CAMPAIGN_ID",
      "identifierValue": "2456167530601"
    },
    {
      "brandGroupId": "23d7c364-0124-410b-b899-8475eddbafef",
      "overrideType": "EXCLUDE",
      "identifierType": "CAMPAIGN_ID",
      "identifierValue": "7286325070001"
    }
  ]
}'
Sample response
A successful request results in a 207 response containing the overrideId for each created override.

Each item in success or error has the index of the item in the original request.

{
  "overrides": {
    "success": [
      {
        "index": 0,
        "override": {
          "brandGroupId": "23d7c364-0124-410b-b899-8475eddbafef",
          "overrideId": "5f47524b-0c20-405e-95c7-abe8965f28b2",
          "overrideType": "INCLUDE",
          "identifierType": "ASIN",
          "identifierValue": "B0018OFKJS",
          "status": "APPROVED"
        }
      },
      {
        "index": 2,
        "override": {
          "brandGroupId": "23d7c364-0124-410b-b899-8475eddbafef",
          "overrideId": "4d493a60-02af-4e49-a318-b8bf1e8cbbae",
          "overrideType": "EXCLUDE",
          "identifierType": "CAMPAIGN_ID",
          "identifierValue": "7286325070001",
          "status": "APPROVED"
        }
      }
    ],
    "error": [
      {
        "index": 1,
        "error": {
          "code": "403",
          "message": "identifierValue not permitted"
        }
      }
    ]
  }
}
Listing overrides
Use the POST /mmm/v1/brandGroupOverrides/list endpoint to get the overrides in your manager account.

You can optionally filter by brandGroupId.

Sample request
curl --location 'https://advertising-api.amazon.com/mmm/v1/brandGroupOverrides/list' \
-H 'Amazon-Advertising-API-ClientId: amzn1.application-oa2-client.xxxxxxxxxx' \
-H 'Amazon-Advertising-API-Manager-Account: amzn1.ads1.ma1.xxxxxxxxxx' \
-H 'Authorization: Bearer Atza|xxxxxxxxxx' \
-H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
-d '{
  "brandGroupIdFilter": {
    "include": [
      "23d7c364-0124-410b-b899-8475eddbafef"
    ]
  }
}'
Sample response
{
  "overrides": [
    {
      "brandGroupId": "23d7c364-0124-410b-b899-8475eddbafef",
      "overrideId": "5f47524b-0c20-405e-95c7-abe8965f28b2",
      "overrideType": "INCLUDE",
      "identifierType": "ASIN",
      "identifierValue": "B0018OFKJS",
      "status": "APPROVED"
    },
    {
      "brandGroupId": "23d7c364-0124-410b-b899-8475eddbafef",
      "overrideId": "4d493a60-02af-4e49-a318-b8bf1e8cbbae",
      "overrideType": "EXCLUDE",
      "identifierType": "CAMPAIGN_ID",
      "identifierValue": "7286325070001",
      "status": "APPROVED"
    }
  ]
}
Deleting overrides
You can delete overrides using the overrideId to restore the default products and campaigns in a brand group.

Use the POST /mmm/v1/brandGroupOverrides/delete endpoint.

Sample request
Up to 100 overrides can be deleted in each request.

curl --location 'https://advertising-api.amazon.com/mmm/v1/brandGroupOverrides/delete' \
-H 'Amazon-Advertising-API-ClientId: amzn1.application-oa2-client.xxxxxxxxxx' \
-H 'Amazon-Advertising-API-Manager-Account: amzn1.ads1.ma1.xxxxxxxxxx' \
-H 'Authorization: Bearer Atza|xxxxxxxxxx' \
-H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
-d '{
  "overrideIdFilter": {
    "include": [
      "4d493a60-02af-4e49-a318-b8bf1e8cbbae",
      "6e2f60a2-95f0-4056-8616-08c7dbdcdb2a"
    ]
  }
}'
Sample response
A successful request results in a 207 response containing the overrideId for each deleted override.

Each item in success or error has the index of the item in the original request.

{
  "overrides": {
    "success": [
      {
        "index": 0,
        "override": {
          "brandGroupId": "23d7c364-0124-410b-b899-8475eddbafef",
          "overrideId": "4d493a60-02af-4e49-a318-b8bf1e8cbbae",
          "overrideType": "EXCLUDE",
          "identifierType": "CAMPAIGN_ID",
          "identifierValue": "7286325070001",
          "status": "APPROVED"
        }
      }
    ],
    "error": [
      {
        "index": 1,
        "error": {
          "code": "404",
          "message": "Not found"
        }
      }
    ]
  }
}
Requesting reports
MMM reports support a variety of different input parameters. See the MMM data feed for more information.

To create a report, use the POST /mmm/v1/reports endpoint.

Sample request
This sample is a report request for media and sales data ranging from 2024-01-01 to 2024-03-31, aggregated to a weekly time unit and postal code geography.

curl --location 'https://advertising-api.amazon.com/mmm/v1/reports' \
-H 'Amazon-Advertising-API-ClientId: amzn1.application-oa2-client.xxxxxxxxxx' \
-H 'Amazon-Advertising-API-Manager-Account: amzn1.ads1.ma1.xxxxxxxxxx' \
-H 'Authorization: Bearer Atza|xxxxxxxxxx' \
-H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
-d '{
  "reportName": "Accent Athletics US Running Shoes Q1 2024",
  "description": "Weekly media & sales by ZIP Code.",
  "configuration": {
    "brandGroupId": "d0145381-b4a9-41a0-83de-e56c8f07d712",
    "metricsType": "MEDIA_AND_SALES",
    "geoDimension": "POSTAL_CODE",
    "timeUnit": "WEEKLY"
  },                    
  "startDate": "2024-01-01",
  "endDate": "2024-03-31",
  "dueDate": "2024-04-15"
}'
Sample response
A successful request results in a 200 response that includes the report. Note down the reportId for use in the following step to check the generation status.

{
  "reportId": "3190da6e-5633-4b9a-b588-acfcdcf4d47e",
  "reportName": "Accent Athletics US Running Shoes Q1 2024",
  "description": "Weekly media & sales by ZIP Code.",
  "configuration": {
    "brandGroupId": "d0145381-b4a9-41a0-83de-e56c8f07d712",
    "metricsType": "MEDIA_AND_SALES",
    "geoDimension": "POSTAL_CODE",
    "timeUnit": "WEEKLY"
  },
  "startDate": "2024-01-01",
  "endDate": "2024-03-31",
  "dueDate": "2024-04-15",
  "status": "PENDING",
  "urls": null,
  "urlsExpireAt": null,
  "failureCode": null,
  "failureMessage": null
}
Checking report status
After you have made a successful request, report generation may take up to 24 hours. Check the report generation status by using the reportId from the create request's response. You will call the GET report endpoint: GET /mmm/v1/reports/{reportId}.

If results are not available within 24 hours, contact mmm-support@amazon.com.

Sample request
curl --location 'https://advertising-api.amazon.com/mmm/v1/reports/3190da6e-5633-4b9a-b588-acfcdcf4d47e' \
-H 'Amazon-Advertising-API-ClientId: amzn1.application-oa2-client.xxxxxxxxxx' \
-H 'Amazon-Advertising-API-Manager-Account: amzn1.ads1.ma1.xxxxxxxxxx' \
-H 'Authorization: Bearer Atza|xxxxxxxxxx' \
-H 'Content-Type: application/json'
A successful call to the GET endpoint returns a 200 status code. You can look at the status field of the response to check if your report has finished generating. Below is a table of possible statuses:

Status	Description
PENDING	Report has been created and is awaiting processing.
PROCESSING	Report is processing.
SUCCEEDED	Report is complete. Check urls for the output files.
FAILED	Report processing failed. Check the failureCode and failureMessage for details.
CANCELED	Report is canceled. Contact mmm-support@amazon.com if this is unexpected.
Downloading reports
After your report's status is SUCCEEDED, it is ready. The urls field of the report's response body contains links to download your report's files. You can make a GET call using cURL or enter the URL in your browser to download the file.

Sample response
{
  "reportId": "3190da6e-5633-4b9a-b588-acfcdcf4d47e",
  "reportName": "Accent Athletics US Running Shoes Q1 2024",
  "description": "Weekly media & sales by ZIP Code.",
  "configuration": {
    "brandGroupId": "d0145381-b4a9-41a0-83de-e56c8f07d712",
    "metricsType": "MEDIA_AND_SALES",
    "geoDimension": "POSTAL_CODE",
    "timeUnit": "WEEKLY"
  },
  "startDate": "2024-01-01",
  "endDate": "2024-03-31",
  "dueDate": "2024-04-15",
  "status": "SUCCEEDED",
  "urls": [
    "https://example.com/3190da6e-5633-4b9a-b588-acfcdcf4d47e/AggregatedSummaryReport.xlsx",
    "https://example.com/3190da6e-5633-4b9a-b588-acfcdcf4d47e/CreativeGrainNationalCampaignPerformanceMetrics.tsv.zip",
    "https://example.com/3190da6e-5633-4b9a-b588-acfcdcf4d47e/SSPANationalCampaignPerformanceMetrics.tsv.zip"
  ],
  "urlsExpireAt": "2024-04-12T09:15:45Z",
  "failureCode": null,
  "failureMessage": null
}
